           в–Ђв–€в–Ђ
           в–„в–€в–„


  The scouring of the chasm scattered its people to the f o u r quadrants o f  t h e

В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·


#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§0
world, sparking t h e
b i r t h  o f  n e w territories and settle-
ments.
  T h r e e  s a i l e d
n o r t h e a s t  and vanished in a labyrinth beneath the sea.
  Five travelled south-

В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·


#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§0
w e s t and erected great monuments and towers that reached to the heavens.
  Two escaped west
a n d mined g r e a t caverns for t h e i r mountain kingdom.
  And o n e  of  t h e

В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·


#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§0
chasmfolk remained near the cradle of life, creating a new home away from the ruins. He was called SomethingSaucy. Soon other refugees and people new to the world were drawn to

В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·


#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§0
the area, joining him in his endeavour.
  The new settlement became known as the Blue City, due to the plentiful deposits of azure stone beneath the ground. Under SomethingSaucy's

В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·


#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§0
g u i d a n c e, the city entered a golden age o f  w e a l t h  a n d splendour.
  T h u s, the f i r s t Ancient came forth.




В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·


#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§0

        в–Ђв–€в–Ђв–€в–Ђ
        в–„в–€в–„в–€в–„


  Among the bluefolk was a man n a m e d Ttocs_Is_Awe.  H e hailed from the wilder-

В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·


#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§0
ness, but was awed by the kindness of  t h e people and saw  t h e Blue City to be more to his liking.
  H e  developed  a n interest in writing and built a house of books for important texts,

В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·


#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§0
becoming its protector f r o m  t h e r e  on. Eventually, he  a l s o became the successor of SomethingSaucy as the leader of  t h e bluefolk.
  Thus, the s e c o n d Ancient came forth.

В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·


#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§0

      в–Ђв–€в–Ђв–€в–Ђв–€в–Ђ
      в–„в–€в–„в–€в–„в–€в–„


  Another man,  t o o, hailed from the wilder-
ness and came to live with the bluefolk. His

В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·


#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§0
name was NateMagic, and he joined the city a f t e r  an invitation from kinsmen already living there. NateMagic was a cunning man and soon  b e c a m e  the warden of the B l u e City, keeping track of

В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·


#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§0
a l l  who entered its gates.
  Thus, t h e  t h i r d Ancient came forth.






В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·


