В§lВ§0В§l  THE TRANSITION

В§4      в•”в•ђв•ђв•¦в•ђв•ђв•— 



          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·


#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§0
It was at  this  point that the Blue City, and its sister city in  the southwest, reached new  h e i g h t s  of success. M o r e than
o n c e  h a d  t h e darkness attempted to pillage and burn, only 

В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·


#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§0
to be fought  b a c k each time by those who had l e a r n e d  the lessons of the chasm.
  B u t  t h e darkness
is not  s o  e a s i l y discouraged.
  It  f o c u s e d new tactics on t h e  Gray

В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·


#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§0
City in the southwest, those proud lords of the many towers that pierce  t h e  clouds, poisoning their minds with promises of power and embroiling them in bitter conflict.
  Watching in horror,

В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·


#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§0
the bluefolk witnessed their sister city tear itself apart, its laws abolished. The Gray City, a  p l a c e  of
f r e e d o m  a n d 
p r o s p e r i t y, was defeated.
  Unable to ignore the

В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·


#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§0
symptoms in their own rule of law, the people of t h e Blue City lost all hope, abandoning their  h o m e s  and
f l e e i n g  to safe havens. The darkness observed; its work was complete.

В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·


#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§0
  Thus the light of the F i r s t  Cities  w a s extinguished, and the Second Age came to an end.





В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·


