В§lВ§0В§l   THE BEGINNING

В§4      в•”в•ђв•ђв•¦в•ђв•ђв•— 



          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·


#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§0
  Of the multitudes who retreated from t h e 
B l u e  City, the man 
n a m e d  NateMagic travelled the furthest. His journey took him to the  f a r t h e s t reaches of his former realm; to  t h e lonely,

В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·


#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§0
frozen metal mines of t h e north. There he sought to find solace from the cruelties of these new times.
  Before the disaster, he had travelled the 
o t h e r  cities  a n d forced people to read

В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·


#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§0
h i s writings. W h e n people were no longer angered by t h i s, he was surprised a n d developed an interest in books.
  A n d so, he bravely set to building a great hall in this distant land

В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·


#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§0
of snow and i c e. This place became l a t e r known as The Citadel.
  Some time later, word of his  n e w  pursuits reached the bluefolk named SomethingSaucy a n d  Ttocs_Is_Awe.
Being of t h e  s a m e

В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·


#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§0
origin and with mutual interests, they decided to join h i m. So they invited some kinsmen 
w i t h them, prepared for the journey and went forth.
  Once there, they ex-
panded the great hall,

В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·


#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§0
now a house of texts, and built a village next to it. Together, all the refugees a n d their 
k i n s m e n started collecting books and writing n e w ones. It was then The Three Ancients reached an

В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·


#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§0
agreement and named themselves.

T h u s,  t h e Maester Alliance came forth.





